In {{ill|Hase-dera (Sakurai)|ja|長谷寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a {{ill|Shingon-shū Buzan-ha|ja|真言宗豊山派|qq=draft|qq=draft}} temple in {{ill|Sakurai City|ja|桜井市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Nara Prefecture, there is another "standing statue of Uhō-dōji" to the left of the main deity, also designated as an Important Cultural Property<ref name="Hase-dera">[https://www.hasedera.or.jp/promotion/1/blog_detail.html?key=entry&value=183 Hase-dera Exhibition at Abeno Harukas Museum], Hase-dera, January 10, 2016</ref>. It is believed to have been created in 1538 (Tenbun 7) by the renowned sculptor Unshū<ref name="Hase-dera"/>.
In {{ill|Senryū-ji (Hokuto City)|ja|泉龍寺 (北杜市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a temple in {{ill|Hokuto City, Yamanashi|ja|北杜市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, there is a suijaku painting of Uhō-dōji from the Muromachi period<ref>Kitamura Hiroshi, ''Takane Historical Sites Guide'', 2012, p.15</ref>. The temple's mountain name (''sangō'') is Rain Treasure Mountain (雨宝山).
