== Characteristics == Uhō-dōji is depicted holding a {{ill|Vajra staff|ja|金剛宝棒|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the right hand and a {{ill|Cintamani|ja|如意宝珠|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the left hand, with a {{ill|Gorintō|ja|五輪塔|1=Gorintō|1=Gorintō|qq=draft|qq=draft}} atop the head<ref name="Daijisen"/><ref name="Daijirin"/><ref name="Nihongo Daijiten"/>.
== Cultural Properties == In {{ill|Kongōshō-ji|ja|金剛證寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a temple of the {{ill|Rinzai sect Nanzen-ji school|ja|臨済宗南禅寺派|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Ise City|ja|伊勢市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Mie Prefecture, there is a "wooden standing statue of Uhō-dōji," designated as an [[Important Cultural Property (Japan)|Important Cultural Property]] on February 8, 1912 (Meiji 45)<ref name="Kongōshō-ji">[https://www.city.ise.mie.jp/cul_spo_edu/culture/bunkazai_shiseki/bunkazai/chokoku/1009576.html Wooden Standing Statue of Uhō-dōji], Ise City</ref>. According to temple tradition, it was carved by {{ill|Kūkai|ja|空海|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in 825 (Tenchō 2). However, the style suggests it dates to the late Heian period<ref name="Kongōshō-ji"/>.
In {{ill|Hase-dera (Sakurai)|ja|長谷寺|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a {{ill|Shingon-shū Buzan-ha|ja|真言宗豊山派|qq=draft|qq=draft}} temple in {{ill|Sakurai City|ja|桜井市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Nara Prefecture, there is another "standing statue of Uhō-dōji" to the left of the main deity, also designated as an Important Cultural Property<ref name="Hase-dera">[https://www.hasedera.or.jp/promotion/1/blog_detail.html?key=entry&value=183 Hase-dera Exhibition at Abeno Harukas Museum], Hase-dera, January 10, 2016</ref>. It is believed to have been created in 1538 (Tenbun 7) by the renowned sculptor Unshū<ref name="Hase-dera"/>.
In {{ill|Senryū-ji (Hokuto City)|ja|泉龍寺 (北杜市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a temple in {{ill|Hokuto City, Yamanashi|ja|北杜市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, there is a suijaku painting of Uhō-dōji from the Muromachi period<ref>Kitamura Hiroshi, ''Takane Historical Sites Guide'', 2012, p.15</ref>. The temple's mountain name (''sangō'') is Rain Treasure Mountain (雨宝山).
